<DOC><DOCNO> AP890529-0084 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-29-89 1319EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Germany-Escape     05-29 0106</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Germany-Escape,0110</SECOND><HEAD>East German Border Guard Escapes to West Germany</HEAD><DATELINE>COBURG, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A 20-year-old East German borderguard abandoned his weapon and climbed over a steel-mesh fence toescape to West Germany, police said Monday.   The soldier ``waited until his supervisor was temporarily gone,then abandoned his sub-machinegun and climbed over the steel-meshfence to escape,'' the Bavarian border police said.   The escape near the Bavarian city of Coburg occurred Friday,police said.   Ten-foot-high chain-link fences constructed by the East Germansseparate the two German nations along their border near Coburg.   Coburg is about 120 miles north of the Bavarian capital, Munich.</TEXT></DOC>